OL,4,CTurkey died after poor care, says
OL,5,Ccoroner
OL,7,FMr Pollard told Ms Agoglia's family he
OL,8,Fwould write to Health Secretary Wes
OL,9,FStreeting, adding: "I do feel
OL,10,Fsomething further needs to be done to
OL,11,Fstop this frankly barbaric medical
OL,12,Fpractice being conducted to such low
OL,13,Fstandards that would certainly not be
OL,14,Ftolerated in the UK."
OL,16,FBolton Coroner's Court heard that Ms
OL,17,FAgoglia, from Little Hulton, had
OL,18,Fstruggled with her mental health and
OL,19,Fwas on medication for ADHD and bipolar
OL,20,Fdisorder.
OL,26,@qD@TOUvD@UO]
